From 169a818cdc529eba42381893cb98e383889a96a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:26 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: Copied MAC to net_dev structure via dev_addr_set

Netdev warning comes if when using memcpy to copy net_dev->dev_addr.
From 5.17 version, net_dev->dev_add should be filled with dev_addr_set
to aviod netdev warning. net_dev->dev_addr MAC gets filled via
dev_addr_set().

Signed-off-by: Rakesh Ravanan <quic_rravanan@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/iface.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/iface.c b/net/mac80211/iface.c
index 062df76..ec97cfe 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/iface.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/iface.c
@@ -2304,6 +2304,7 @@ int ieee80211_if_add(struct ieee80211_local *local, const char *name,
 		}
 
 		ieee80211_assign_perm_addr(local, ndev->perm_addr, type);
+		ndev->addr_len = ETH_ALEN;
 		if (is_valid_ether_addr(params->macaddr))
 #if KERNEL_VERSION(5, 17, 0) > LINUX_VERSION_CODE
 			memcpy(ndev->dev_addr, params->macaddr, ETH_ALEN);
-- 
2.34.1

